### Function to Check if Any Number in an Array is a Prime Number

Here is a JavaScript function that takes an array of five numbers as input and checks if any of the numbers is a prime number. If it is, the function prints the number to the console.

```javascript
function checkPrimeNumbers(arr) {
  // Loop through each number in the array
  for (let num of arr) {
    // Check if the number is prime
    if (isPrime(num)) {
      console.log(`The number ${num} is a prime number.`);
    }
  }
}

// Function to check if a number is prime
function isPrime(num) {
  // Check if the number is less than 2
  if (num < 2) {
    return false;
  }

  // Check if the number is divisible by any number between 2 and its square root
  for (let i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(num); i++) {
    if (num % i === 0) {
      return false;
    }
  }

  // If the number is not divisible by any number between 2 and its square root, it is prime
  return true;
}
```

### How the Function Works

